<a href="https://lithub.com/lit-hub-daily-september-23-2024/"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-243237 size-thumbnail" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/Marginalia_5095211566-150x150.jpg" alt="marginalia" width="150" height="150" /></a>
<ul>
 	<li><a href="https://splitlipthemag.com/memoir/0924/kasey-butcher-santana?src=longreads" class="external" target="_blank"><span style="font-weight: 400">The marginalia of prison library books</span></a></li>
 	<li><a href="https://www.newyorker.com/books/second-read/the-pornographer-reissue-john-mcgahern-review" class="external" target="_blank"><span style="font-weight: 400">Jessica Winter revisits John McGahern’s fathers</span></a></li>
 	<li><a href="https://www.vulture.com/article/sally-rooney-intermezzo-new-book-romance-novels-marxism-capitalism.html" class="external" target="_blank"><span style="font-weight: 400">Andrea Long Chu on Sally Rooney</span></a></li>
</ul>
